<Class name="CnEcBaseRoot" id="33ec00a5-17b8-48b6-adec-ead04ef77c05">
    <superclass name="CnEcBaseEntity"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>___________________________________________________________________________

              P R O P R I E T A R Y   N O T I C E

This software, in whole and in every part, is proprietary to Jade Software
Corporation Limited at Christchurch, New Zealand and is not to be
reproduced, used or disclosed except upon prior written permission of Jade
Software Corporation Limited.

  COPYRIGHT © JADE SOFTWARE CORPORATION LIMITED 2004 - ALL RIGHTS RESERVED
____________________________________________________________________________

A singleton instance of this class is used as the Root for BaseSchema's
concrete objects.  To instantiate this class for a subschema application,
invoke the app.cnEcSetBaseRoot method from your application's own
"initialize" method.
	app.cnEcSetBaseRoot(pIsCreateIfNotFound:Boolean):Boolean updating;

If the pIsCreateIfNotFound parameter is true, and if an instance of the
CnEcBaseRoot class isn't found, then one will be created (note that this
will require a database transaction).  A boolean flag will be returned
to indicate whether or not the set was successful.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="basemap"/>
